oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: World War II Veteran, George Warren, hunting near Davidson County, Tenn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of George Warren (a World War II veteran) hunting near Davidson County, Tennessee. Warren is holding a shotgun and wearing a hat, long-sleeve shirt and light-colored pants. Warren has shot two rabbits and one squirrel. He is standing in a field with trees and brush in the background.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
